The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Panaji, Jan. 7 (PTI): The Goa tourism department has decided to censor all advertisements showing bikini-clad women to fight the image of Goa as a sex-tourism destination.           
	Tourism minister Fransisco Pacheco said he would ask all tour operators to follow the guidelines on advertisements.                   
	 Madurai (PTI): The CBI has arrested the president of the Tamil Nadu Chamber of Commerce and Industry, V. Neethi Mohan, and four others in connection with alleged diversion of potassium chloride from a unit in Karaikal to make raw materials for explosives. The five have been remanded in judicial custody.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI):The anti-narcotics cell has arrested a former homeguard and a drug peddler with 150kg of narcotics. Sleuths intercepted their vehicle and recovered the drugs, worth Rs 4.5 lakh, from a cavity in the backseat.                   
	 Panaji (PTI): Goa politician John Fernandes, accused of raping a Russian girl, was remanded in seven days police custody by a local court on Thursday. He had surrendered before the crime branch on Wednesday after being in hiding for almost a month.                   
	Mainpuri (PTI): The Reserve Bank of India has lodged a complaint against an SBI branch for allegedly depositing two fake Rs 500 notes with it, police said. The RBI had earlier detected six fake notes in the cash chest sent by SBI, Bhogaon.                  
	 Porayar (PTI): Three persons were killed and 25 injured in an accident at Nagapattinam in Tamil Nadu on Thursday. A Tamil Nadu State Transport Corporation bus had rammed into another bus parked on the roadside around 3.45am.
                                                                                                                                              
